    "body": "Please reconsider, the patch is trivial, doesn't break anything because behaviour doesn't change and this issue is causing real problems in our systems, as people are not regularly allowed to change the shared HDF5 files. I hate to sprinkle `mode='r'` all over the place, in particular as `read_hdf(f, mode='r')` just sounds broken ...\n"
